Material Information Summary:

Project Highlights (Grønnedal REE Project):

  • Mineralogy: Dominant synchysite, bastnasite, and monazite – ideal for Nd-Pr permanent magnet feedstock.
  • Resource: 89Mt inferred resource (6,363ppm TREO), representing ~6% of the carbonatite body.
  • Key Grades:
  • Niobium up to 4,670ppm (pyrochlore/columbite).
  • Yttrium up to 777ppm (xenotime/fergusonite).
  • HREE credits (Dy, Tb, Y).
  • Liberation: Up to 54.4% liberation for synchysite/bastnasite, coarse grain size (P80: 19–205µm), supporting low-cost flotation.
  • Location: Greenland (deep-water port access, no uranium constraints).

Strategic Advantages:

  • Processing: Amenable to conventional flotation/magnetic separation (similar to Mountain Pass/USA and Mount Weld/Australia).
  • Growth Potential: Only 6% of the carbonatite drilled; 8km x 3km intrusion mapped.
  • Geopolitical: Aligns with EU/US critical minerals supply chain diversification.

Next Steps:

  • Metallurgical studies (flotation, leaching, EPMA) to advance toward pre-feasibility.

Financial/Operational Impact:

  • No capital raising or financial figures disclosed. Focus on resource/resource potential.

Note: No trading halt, capital raising, or immediate financial data requiring action. Material upside hinges on successful metallurgical outcomes and resource expansion.

Material Information Summary – Aurelia Metals (ASX: AMI) FY26 Guidance & Outlook

Production Guidance (FY26) & Aspirational Outlook (FY27/28)

  • Gold (k oz):
  • FY26: 35–45 | FY27: 43–53 | FY28: 30–40
  • Copper (k t):
  • FY26: 3.0–4.0 | FY27: 3.0–4.5 | FY28: 6.0–8.0 (notable FY28 ramp-up)
  • Zinc (k t):
  • FY26: 24–32 | FY27: 24–32 | FY28: 40–50 (material FY28 increase)
  • Lead (k t):
  • FY26: 14–22 | FY27: 14–22 | FY28: 23–33

Operational Highlights

  • Peak Mine (FY26): 530–580kt planned; grades declining until FY28 transition to Great Cobar (new primary ore source).
  • Federation Mine: Commercial production from 1 July 2025. Ramp-up to 600ktpa by FY27; FY26 target: 320–340kt.

Costs (FY26 Guidance)

  • Group Operating Costs: $275–315M (vs. FY25: $185–220M).
  • Peak Costs: $185–205M (higher development/throughput).
  • Federation Costs: $70–80M (now operational vs. FY25 growth capex).

Capital Expenditure (FY26)

  • Sustaining Capex: $50–60M (includes equipment rebuilds).
  • Growth Capex: $60–75M (Federation completion + Great Cobar development).
  • Exploration Spend: $13–18M.

Key Forward-Looking Risks

  • FY27/28 Targets Aspirational – Subject to execution (Great Cobar start-up, plant expansion).
  • Cost Inflation Exposure – Higher sustaining/growth capex in FY26.

Note: Outlook statements are non-binding ("indicative only"). Focus on FY26 guidance for near-term trading.
